div.p:

   Anſwer. 
 Firſt, I would deſire to know, Whether the Baptiſme which you adminiſter regenerates and ſaves, or no. (I meane ſacramentally, for we ſay ours regenerates) If no, then it is not the Baptiſme that Chriſt & his Apoſtles uſed,1 Pet. 3. for Peter ſaith, it ſaved;


Paul ſaith, it buried with Chriſt. If yea,Rom. 6. whether you beleeve that all that are baptized of you, are certainly regenerate and ſaved, or no; and then tell us, what is the ground of your beliefe.

Secondly, but for the fuller proofe of the point, that children of parents whereof the one at leaſt is a beleever, are holy, that place, 1 Cor. 7.14. is moſt direct and cleare, where the Apoſtle ſaith, For the unbeleeving husband is ſanctified by the wife;

                           〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                        . and the unbeleeving wife is ſanctified by the husband; elſe were your children uncleane, but now they are holy; whence we may note,

Anſw. If the ſame be the rule or ground for juſtification and ſalvation, and for baptiſme: then muſt Miniſters have no rule for baptiſme, unleſſe they can know the heart, as God who juſtifies and ſaves; and ſo conſequently the baptizer muſt either be (
   〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
) the knower of the heart, that is God alone;Act 1.24. or baptize beſide or without rule, that is unlawfully; for the true holyneſſe that accompanies the new creature and ſaving faith, is known to none but God and the ſpirit of man which is in him.1. Cor. 2.11.
